.TH CYGNUS 1.6-2 "March 2026" "Version 1.6-2" "Cygnus Window Manager"
.SH NAME
cygnus \- a minimalistic floating window manager for X11

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cygnus

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cygnus
is a thin, minimalistic window manager for X11 written in C. It provides basic floating window management with a focus on simplicity and keyboard-driven interaction. Windows are managed via MapRequest and ConfigureRequest events and feature thin borders without title bars or buttons.

Cygnus features a built-in panel that is always visible and cannot be covered by windows. It also includes a built-in application runner and a configurable root menu.

.SH KEY BINDINGS
Cygnus uses Alt (Mod1) as the default modifier for window management and Ctrl/Shift/Super for system actions.

.TP
.B Alt+q
Close the focused window.
.TP
.B Alt+F4
Close the focused window.
.TP
.B Alt+x
Maximize the focused window (toggles).
.TP
.B Alt+n
Minimize the focused window (iconify).
.TP
.B Alt+r
Restore the focused window from maximized state.
.TP
.B Alt+Tab
Cycle through managed windows and bring them to the front.
.TP
.B F11
Toggle fullscreen for the focused window.
.TP
.B F5
Refresh borders and update window colors.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+q
Exit the window manager.
.TP
.B Ctrl+d
Launch the built-in application runner.
.TP
.B Alt+Return
Launch x-terminal-emulator (default).
.TP
.B Alt+f
Launch the built-in file manager (cygnus-fm).

.SH MOUSE INTERACTIONS
.TP
.B Right Click (Desktop)
Open the root menu.
.TP
.B Alt + Left Click Drag
Move the window currently under the cursor.
.TP
.B Ctrl + Left Click Drag
Resize the window currently under the cursor from the nearest corner.

.SH CONFIGURATION
Cygnus looks for configuration files in the user's home directory.

.TP
.B ~/.cygnus-wm/session
A shell script executed on startup. Use this to set the wallpaper, start a panel (e.g., stalonetray), or launch background daemons. Must be executable.
.TP
.B ~/.cygnus-wm/keys
A plain text file for defining additional key bindings.
Format: [MODIFIER] [KEYSYM] [COMMAND]
Supported modifiers: Control, Ctrl, Alt, Mod1, Shift, Super, Mod4.
Internal commands: run (triggers the built-in runner).
Example:
  Super Super_L run
  Alt Return x-terminal-emulator
  Control space x-terminal-emulator

.TP
.B ~/.cygnus-wm/menu
A plain text file for defining the root menu.
Format:
  [exec] (Label) {command}
  [exit]
  [restart]
Internal commands: {run} (triggers the built-in runner).
Example:
  [exec] (Terminal) {x-terminal-emulator}
  [exec] (Run) {run}
  [restart]
  [exit]

.TP
.B ~/.cygnus-wm/icons
A plain text file for configuring the file manager icon theme.
Format: icontheme=NAME
Example:
  icontheme=ubuntu-mono-dark

